  "title": "Current-carrying wires - force on wire in B-field",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a wire, which carries a current I toward the bottom of the page and to the right, in a magnetic field that is directed into the page.\" src=\"/images/7567362495df719c5ea3847d2f2c915d.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A long straight wire lies in the plane of the page and carries a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. The wire lies in a region containing a magnetic field directed into the page and the magnetic force exerted on the wire is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The wire is then rotated such that the current is directed toward the bottom of the page. The magnetic force exerted on the wire in this orientation is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and provides correct justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0 is greater than F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0 is greater than F sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because after the wire is rotated the angle between the magnetic field and the wire is zero.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0 is greater than F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0 is greater than F sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because after the wire is rotated the magnetic field strength will decrease because of the magnetic field produced by the current in the wire.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0 equals F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0 equals F sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because after the wire is rotated, the wire is still perpendicular to the magnetic field.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0 equals F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0 equals F sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because the magnetic force exerted on the wire is independent of the angle between the current direction and the magnetic field.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
